sec.p:
Oceanic pCO2 is solved at prescribed surface temperatures, and salinities94, and air-sea fluxes of CO2 are calculated using a prescribed gas transfer velocity. Carbon is exchanged between the ocean and an atmospheric box that can be set to a fixed CO2 value (280.0 μatm) for model equilibration or allowed to vary in time depending on the air-sea carbon partitioning. Parameter values are given in Table 1.Table 1
